               <interp inst="t16871012-10" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/16871012"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16871012-10" type="date" value="16871012"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16871012-10-off49-c48" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871012-10-defend64 t16871012-10-off49 t16871012-10-verdict53"></join>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16871012-10-defend64" type="defendantName">
                     Elizabeth 
                     Wood
                  <interp inst="t16871012-10-defend64" type="surname" value="Wood"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16871012-10-defend64" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16871012-10-defend64" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was Tryed for <rs id="t16871012-10-off49" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16871012-10-off49" type="offenceCategory" value="damage"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16871012-10-off49" type="offenceSubcategory" value="arson"></interp>
               firing the house of 
                     
                        <persName id="t16871012-10-victim66" type="victimName">
                           Robert 
                           Smith
                        <interp inst="t16871012-10-victim66" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16871012-10-victim66" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16871012-10-victim66" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871012-10-off49 t16871012-10-victim66"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                   Scituate in the Parish of <placeName id="t16871012-10-crimeloc50">St. Giles's Criplegate</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t16871012-10-crimeloc50" type="placeName" value="St. Giles's Criplegate"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16871012-10-crimeloc50" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871012-10-off49 t16871012-10-crimeloc50"></join>
               
                  </rs> on the <rs id="t16871012-10-cd51" type="crimeDate">1st. of October</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871012-10-off49 t16871012-10-cd51"></join>: upon Tryal it appeared that a Smoak being discovered, and search made between the Tiles and the Cieling, a Board was found on Fire, and the Prisoner who lived with the Prosecutor in the Nature of a <rs id="t16871012-10-deflabel52" type="occupation">Servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t16871012-10-defend64 t16871012-10-deflabel52"></join> examined, she confessed she had set it on Fire with a Candle, but in Court pleading that she did it accidentally, forgetting her Candle upon being hastily called away with which she had been looking for 1 s. 6 d. she had laid there, and it not appearing she did it designedly or maliciously, she was <rs id="t16871012-10-verdict53" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16871012-10-verdict53" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
